<br>
1) Retains any special attacks, such as poison.<br>
2) <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>May</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, based on my readings of the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Beast Lord Forum</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, start with the base hitpoint of the underlying creature, to which the level/HP buffs are <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>added</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, not simply over writing the original stats.  I cannot be certain about this.<br>
3) Persists after the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Beast Lord</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> zones, i.e. you have created a powerful and likely hostile NPC, not your every day moss snake to say the least.<br>
4) With puppets strings and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /duel</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, may be applied to <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>player</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> characters as well, making <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Beast Lords</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> the ultimate power levellers under some circumstances.  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> &quot;Attack of the 50 Foot Halfling,&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> anyone?<br>
