</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unecridious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Necridious</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 99<br> <font color=#333333>(7/4/02 4:06:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=259.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Beastlords Complete Healing their Pets</span><hr size=1> One Final thing to point out.<br>
<br>
Beastlord pets are sad without the buff.  The pet itself is free to cast, but if you want to have it actually able to fight, you have to buff it.  Saying that the pets zone and are free to cast is really just a gimmick, the pets are just fluff without the level buff, which is comparable to the magician pet spells by itself.<br>
<br>
As using the pet buff as a CH resets all the buffs on the pet, this only slightly different than chain-summoning pets to kill a mob.  Lets do a cursory look at the spells in question at various levels, Necromancer pets thrown in for completness:<br>
<br>
Level 16 B Pet  75m                  Cast time 3 secs<br>
Level 16 M Pet 160m                Cast time 9 secs<br>
Level 16 N Pet 160m                Cast time 9 secs<br>
<br>
Level 29 B Pet 150m                 Cast time 6 secs<br>
Level 29 M Pet 200m                Cast time 10 secs<br>
Level 29 N Pet 290m                Cast time 12 secs<br>
<br>
Level 49 B Pet  250m               Cast time  10 secs<br>
Level 49 M Pet 200m                Cast time 10 secs<br>
Level 49 N Pet 490m                 Cast time 16 secs<br>
<br>
Level 58 B Pet 400m                 Cast time 16 secs<br>
Level 60 M Pet 400m                 Cast time 10 secs<br>
Level 59 N Pet 650m                 Cast time 16 secs<br>
<br>
Mage Epic pet 500m                 Cast time 5 secs+ Orb Cast time<br>
<br>
Other notable differences are that new pets cost Malachite while pet buff is free, and that there is no need to transfer aggro or time a BL pet buff, while the Mage must do so.  On the other hand, there is no recast time for summoning a new pet, while the BL pet buff has a slight recast, and that if the pet should actually die, the BL now has to summon another pet with the skill, adding several seconds onto the cast time, as well as having to channel not only the summons but the buff as well- assuming the mob doesn't kill the new green pet out of hand before returning to beat you some more.<br>
<br>
I'd say from the comparison above it's kind of a non issue, there is a pretty big advantage for the BL at early levels, but later on they even out, and eventually the favor swings to Mages, though not to the point it was at for BL in the beginning.<br>
<br>
My point is that if chain casting is fair, this is little different, though much easier for the BL to do.  The only question would remain would be how strong are BL pets, and is their relative weakness worth the reduced mana and cast time at early levels.<br>
<br>
<br>
On an unrelated side note, while I can see where some mages would complain about the epic at 500m when most your pets were 200m, I'd have to point them to the Necro's non epic pets.... <p><img src=http://personal.atl.bellsouth.net/atl/d/a/dastorys/Pictures/Necsig.jpg>

